# Per-Dockerfile ignore file for the scaffolder clean-room gate-runner build
# (context = repo root, dockerfile =
# oss/packages/create-agentic-app/e2e/Dockerfile).
#
# Docker/BuildKit looks for `<context-relative-dockerfile-path>.dockerignore`
# at the context root before falling back to a root `.dockerignore` —
# verified empirically in this environment (Docker 29.4.3 / Compose
# v2.40.3). Using that lookup here, instead of touching the repo's existing
# root `.dockerignore`, is intentional: that file is a leftover include-only
# allowlist from a pre-restructure repo layout (it whitelists `packages/`,
# `core/`, `internal/` — none of which exist at this repo's top level
# anymore) and nothing in the Makefile currently builds with plain repo-root
# context, so extending it risked resurrecting dead config for an unrelated
# surface. This file is scoped to exactly this one build.
#
# `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` at repo root needs every workspace
# member's package.json present (pnpm-workspace.yaml spans the whole
# monorepo), so this does NOT scope down to just the cohort packages — it
# excludes only what the install/build/publish/scaffold sequence in
# run-gate.mjs never reads:
#   - node_modules (every workspace member's) — reinstalled fresh inside the
#     image by run-gate.mjs; shipping the host's copies would fight pnpm's
#     own resolution and bloat the context by multiple GB for nothing.
#   - .git — VCS metadata, not needed for install/build.
#   - build/cache output regenerated by run-gate.mjs's own build step
#     (.next, .turbo, dist, build, coverage, tsbuildinfo caches) — some
#     individually (e.g. apps/platform/.next) approach 1GB and would
#     otherwise dominate the context.
#   - Amplify-generated artifacts (amplify_outputs.json,
#     amplifyconfiguration.json, .amplify/) — irrelevant to the scaffolder
#     and, being environment config, not something to bake into an image.
#   - E2E/test run artifacts (e2e-results, playwright-report, test-results,
#     blob-report) — reruns of unrelated suites, not source.
#   - Secrets: every `.env*` file. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (the only secret this
#     gate ever touches, and only for the optional Task 2 real-LLM hook)
#     reaches the container solely via docker-compose.yml's `environment:`
#     pass-through — it must never be baked into the image layer.

**/node_modules
.git
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/build
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/.amplify
amplify_outputs.json
amplifyconfiguration.json
e2e-results
playwright-report
test-results
blob-report
storybook-static
.pnpm-store
.cache
tmp
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store

# Secrets — never bake env files into the image.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
